=Discussion=

Bob Haugen:

"Value Equations are one of the key concepts that (as far as I know)
originated in [[Sensorica]]. They are democratic agreements on how to
distribute income from collaborative work. I think they are a key
element of governance. Not sure if they belong in a license, but they
were mentioned in Michel's accounting page cited below, and are
related to .

They have been implemented in software, in a working prototype stage.


You can read about the software here:

# https://speakerdeck.com/player/a9a3be6149594d2491286f1888286d89#
# https://speakerdeck.com/player/24d2c288ecc64262a55b3fc539f90564#


And some of the background here (the links in the slides do not work
in speakerdeck, unfortunately):

* http://valuenetwork.referata.com/wiki/The_Value_Equation#Background


Note that the software does not yet implement all of the ideas in the
background discussions.

[[Enspiral]] does things quite differently, as do other groups. Lots of
conversations are going on about these topics now, for example:
https://github.com/open-app/holodex/issues/61 . "

(email, June 2015)



